t day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Nickolas","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: variant spelling of   Nicholas  , influenced by the short form   Nick ."]},{"name":"Nicolas","meanings":["From Late Greek.  See  <b>Nicholas</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":17,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Nicholas Rede was born in 1365, in Somerset, England, his father, Thomas Rede, was 30 and his mother, Mrs. Rede, was 25. He married Unknown Parnel. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1438, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1365–1438":"1365–1438","1368–1434":"1368–1434","1395–1434":"1395–1434","1335–1366":"1335–1366","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1434":"1434","1335":"1335","1368":"1368","1366":"1366","1365":"1365","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1438":"1438","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tiverton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Tiverton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cherestaunton, Somerset, England":"Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1365–1438":"1365–1438","1368–1434":"1368–1434","1395–1434":"1395–1434","1335–1366":"1335–1366","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1434":"1434","1335":"1335","1368":"1368","1366":"1366","1365":"1365","1395":"1395","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1438":"1438","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tiverton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Tiverton, Devon